            <section id="overview">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    The <strong>WebSearchResult</strong> model (Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/WebSearchResult.pm) 
                    provides a database schema for storing and managing web search results in the Comserv application. It is a DBIx::Class Result class that supports:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Capture and storage of search results from multiple sources (web, arxiv, GitHub, StackOverflow, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Multi-stage verification workflow (unverified → verified/rejected)</li>
                    <li>User association (who found the result, who verified it)</li>
                    <li>Rich content storage (snippet + full content)</li>
                    <li>Integration with AI messages for citation tracking</li>
                    <li>Automatic timestamp management (created_at, verified_at)</li>
                    <li>Role-based verification permissions (admin-only verification)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    WebSearchResult serves as a critical component of the Documentation and Knowledge Management System (E.2 integration), 
                    allowing the application to store, verify, and cite external web sources in AI-generated responses.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="schema">
                <h2>Database Schema & Fields</h2>
                
                <h3>Table: websearchresult</h3>
                <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Store web search results, source metadata, and verification status</p>
                <p><strong>Primary Key:</strong> id (auto-increment)</p>
                <p><strong>Key Indexes:</strong> None explicitly defined (consider adding on found_by_user_id, verified_by_user_id)</p>
                
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Field Name</th>
                        <th>Data Type</th>
                        <th>Nullable</th>
                        <th>Default</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>auto_increment</td>
                        <td>Primary key - auto-generated result ID</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>query</td>
                        <td>VARCHAR(500)</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>Search query that produced this result (REQUIRED, up to 500 chars)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>result_title</td>
                        <td>VARCHAR(512)</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>Title/heading of the search result (REQUIRED, up to 512 chars)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>result_url</td>
                        <td>VARCHAR(1000)</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>URL of the search result (REQUIRED, up to 1000 chars)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>result_snippet</td>
                        <td>LONGTEXT</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>Short excerpt from result (REQUIRED, unlimited length)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>full_content</td>
                        <td>LONGTEXT</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Complete content from the result page (optional, populated after full fetch)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>source_type</td>
                        <td>ENUM</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>'web'</td>
                        <td>Source type: 'web', 'public_domain_book', 'arxiv', 'github', 'stackoverflow' (default: 'web')</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>found_by_user_id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>Foreign key to User table - who discovered this result (REQUIRED)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>is_verified</td>
                        <td>BOOLEAN</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>0</td>
                        <td>Verification status: 0=unverified, 1=verified, -1=rejected (default: 0)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>verified_by_user_id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Foreign key to User table - admin who verified this result (optional)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>verification_notes</td>
                        <td>TEXT</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Notes from verifier (reason for verification/rejection)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>created_at</td>
                        <td>TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>Timestamp when result was discovered (auto-set)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>verified_at</td>
                        <td>TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Timestamp when result was verified/rejected (optional)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>used_in_ai_message_id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Foreign key to AiMessage table - if cited in AI response (optional)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </section>

            <section id="source-types">
                <h2>Supported Source Types</h2>
                <p>WebSearchResult supports 5 different source types to handle diverse information sources:</p>
                
                <h3>Web Sources</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>'web':</strong> Standard web pages from search engines (default)</li>
                    <li><strong>'public_domain_book':</strong> Results from Project Gutenberg or similar public domain sources</li>
                    <li><strong>'arxiv':</strong> Academic papers from arXiv.org (preprints and published papers)</li>
                    <li><strong>'github':</strong> Code repositories and documentation from GitHub</li>
                    <li><strong>'stackoverflow':</strong> Questions and answers from StackOverflow</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Source Type Usage</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $result = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->create({
    query => 'Perl Catalyst authentication',
    result_title => 'Authentication in Catalyst',
    result_url => 'https://github.com/Catalyst/Catalyst-Runtime',
    result_snippet => 'Catalyst provides built-in authentication plugins...',
    source_type => 'github',
    found_by_user_id => 42
});

# Query by source type
my @academic = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    source_type => 'arxiv'
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="verification-workflow">
                <h2>Verification Workflow</h2>
                
                <h3>Verification States</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>is_verified = 0 (UNVERIFIED):</strong> Initial state when result is discovered. Requires admin review.</li>
                    <li><strong>is_verified = 1 (VERIFIED):</strong> Result approved by admin. Safe to cite in AI responses.</li>
                    <li><strong>is_verified = -1 (REJECTED):</strong> Result flagged as inaccurate or inappropriate. Should not be cited.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Typical Verification Flow</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Discovery:</strong> Search result captured → is_verified = 0 (unverified)</li>
                    <li><strong>Admin Review:</strong> Admin evaluates result quality and accuracy</li>
                    <li><strong>Decision:</strong> Admin approves (verified=1) or rejects (verified=-1) with notes</li>
                    <li><strong>Timestamping:</strong> verified_at and verified_by_user_id recorded</li>
                    <li><strong>Citation:</strong> Only verified results (is_verified=1) can be cited in AI messages</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Helper Methods</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>is_pending_verification():</strong> Check if result needs admin review</p>
                    <pre><code>if ($result->is_pending_verification) {
    print "Waiting for admin approval\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>can_be_verified($user_role):</strong> Check if user can verify results</p>
                    <pre><code>if ($result->can_be_verified($user->role)) {
    # Show verification UI
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>mark_as_verified($user_id, $notes):</strong> Approve result</p>
                    <pre><code>$result->mark_as_verified(42, 'Accurate and relevant source');</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>mark_as_rejected($user_id, $notes):</strong> Reject result</p>
                    <pre><code>$result->mark_as_rejected(42, 'Outdated information - 2015 version');</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="relationships">
                <h2>User Relationships & References</h2>
                
                <h3>Many-to-One Relationships</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>belongs_to 'found_by_user':</strong> User who discovered this result
                        <ul>
                            <li>Foreign Key: WebSearchResult.found_by_user_id → User.id</li>
                            <li>Usage: <code>my $finder = $result->found_by_user;</code></li>
                            <li>Purpose: Audit trail of who added the result</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>belongs_to 'verified_by_user':</strong> Admin who approved/rejected result (optional, left join)
                        <ul>
                            <li>Foreign Key: WebSearchResult.verified_by_user_id → User.id (LEFT JOIN)</li>
                            <li>Usage: <code>my $approver = $result->verified_by_user;</code></li>
                            <li>Purpose: Track who made verification decision</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>belongs_to 'ai_message':</strong> AI message that cited this result (optional, left join)
                        <ul>
                            <li>Foreign Key: WebSearchResult.used_in_ai_message_id → AiMessage.id (LEFT JOIN)</li>
                            <li>Usage: <code>my $citation = $result->ai_message;</code></li>
                            <li>Purpose: Track where results are used in AI responses</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="api-methods">
                <h2>API Methods & Helpers</h2>
                
                <h3>Standard DBIx::Class Methods</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Creating Results:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $result = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->create({
    query => 'Perl DBI tutorial',
    result_title => 'DBI Perl Database Interface',
    result_url => 'https://dbi.perl.org/',
    result_snippet => 'The DBI is the standard Perl interface to databases...',
    source_type => 'web',
    found_by_user_id => 42
});</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Retrieving Results:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $result = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->find(100);

my @unverified = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    is_verified => 0
})->all;

my @verified = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    is_verified => 1
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Updating Results:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>$result->update({
    full_content => $fetched_page_content
});

$result->result_snippet('Updated snippet...');
$result->source_type('arxiv');
$result->update;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Query Patterns</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Find by Query:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my @results = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    query => 'Catalyst web framework'
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Find Cited Results:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my @cited = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    used_in_ai_message_id => { '!=' => undef }
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Find Awaiting Verification:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my @pending = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    is_verified => 0
}, {
    order_by => { -asc => 'created_at' }
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="examples">
                <h2>Usage Examples</h2>
                
                <h3>Example 1: Store Search Result from Web Search</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>use JSON::MaybeXS;

my $search_result = {
    title => 'Introduction to Perl Regular Expressions',
    url => 'https://perldoc.perl.org/perlre',
    snippet => 'Perl regular expressions are powerful pattern matching...',
    query => 'Perl regex tutorial'
};

my $stored = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->create({
    query => $search_result->{query},
    result_title => $search_result->{title},
    result_url => $search_result->{url},
    result_snippet => $search_result->{snippet},
    source_type => 'web',
    found_by_user_id => $current_user->id
});

print "Stored result #" . $stored->id . " awaiting verification\n";</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 2: Admin Verification Workflow</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my @pending = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    is_verified => 0
}, { 
    order_by => { -asc => 'created_at' },
    rows => 10
})->all;

foreach my $result (@pending) {
    my $finder = $result->found_by_user;
    print "Result: " . $result->result_title . "\n";
    print "Found by: " . $finder->username . "\n";
    print "Source: " . $result->source_type . "\n";
    
    if ($is_admin && $is_valid) {
        $result->mark_as_verified(
            $admin_user->id,
            'Verified - reputable source'
        );
    }
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 3: Citation in AI Message</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $verified = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    is_verified => 1,
    source_type => 'arxiv'
})->first;

if ($verified) {
    my $ai_message = $schema->resultset('AiMessage')->create({
        conversation_id => $conv_id,
        role => 'assistant',
        content => 'According to the paper...',
        sources_cited => JSON::MaybeXS::encode_json([$verified->id])
    });
    
    $verified->update({
        used_in_ai_message_id => $ai_message->id
    });
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 4: Reject Inaccurate Result</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $result = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->find(456);

if ($result->is_pending_verification) {
    my $admin = $schema->resultset('User')->find(10);
    
    $result->mark_as_rejected(
        $admin->id,
        'Source no longer maintained - last update 2018'
    );
    
    print "Result rejected: " . $result->verification_notes . "\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 5: Fetch and Update Full Content</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>use LWP::UserAgent;

my $result = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->find(200);

my $ua = LWP::UserAgent->new;
my $response = $ua->get($result->result_url);

if ($response->is_success) {
    $result->update({
        full_content => $response->content
    });
    print "Content fetched and stored\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="troubleshooting">
                <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
                
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <h3>Issue 1: Verification Status Not Updating</h3>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> After calling mark_as_verified(), the result still shows is_verified=0</p>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Helper method doesn't explicitly save; need to verify update() succeeded</p>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $success = $result->mark_as_verified($admin_id, 'notes');
if (!$success) {
    warn "Update failed: " . $result->error;
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <h3>Issue 2: NULL verified_by_user Relationship</h3>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Calling $result->verified_by_user returns undef for unverified results</p>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> verified_by_user_id is NULL until verified; relationship uses LEFT JOIN</p>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $verifier = $result->verified_by_user;
my $verifier_name = $verifier ? $verifier->username : 'Pending';</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <h3>Issue 3: Large Snippets Causing Display Issues</h3>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> result_snippet with 10K+ characters breaks UI layout</p>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> LONGTEXT field allows unlimited size; no truncation in model</p>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $preview = substr($result->result_snippet, 0, 500) . '...';
# Or add method to model for consistent truncation</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <h3>Issue 4: Orphaned Results (used_in_ai_message_id points to deleted message)</h3>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Result references AI message that was deleted</p>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> No cascade delete; manual cleanup needed</p>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code># Find orphaned results
my @orphaned = $schema->resultset('WebSearchResult')->search({
    used_in_ai_message_id => { '!=' => undef }
})->all;

foreach my $result (@orphaned) {
    unless ($result->ai_message) {
        $result->update({ used_in_ai_message_id => undef });
    }
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <h3>Issue 5: URL Length Exceeding 1000 Characters</h3>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Error: "result_url exceeds max length 1000"</p>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Some URLs with query strings are very long</p>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $url = $long_url;
if (length($url) > 1000) {
    # Store short URL, full URL in metadata
    my $short = substr($url, 0, 990);
    $result->result_url($short);
}
# Or use URL shortening service</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

